script: Guys, I’m literally cruising through Dublin’s buzzing streets on a moving bus, and wow—brick buildings, a cozy hotel, a lively restaurant, and a school all lining the road, while people and buses swirl around me—this city’s energy is off the charts, and I can’t wait to share every heartbeat with you right now, as the sun paints the sky, and the Guinness pubs beckon.
Zooming past, I spot H&M’s bright window displays.

Stepping onto the cobblestones, I feel the city pulse. A double‑decker bus glides by, its red paint gleaming. Crowds weave past, each face a story waiting to be shared. I capture every moment, excitement.
Suddenly, a bright yellow DUKW tour bus rolls by, its chrome gleaming. Nearby, the spires of Christ Church Cathedral loom, adding timeless charm.
I stepped onto cobblestones, feeling historic pulse beneath my feet, spotting the iconic Hard Rock sign.
Suddenly, street lights flicker, painting the red pub in warm glow.
